    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "The village grew around the Watertown and Rome railroad, a key commerce route in northern New York.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        3
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.villageoflacona.com/about.html"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "The former Lacona Depot has been restored and now houses the Village of Lacona and Village of Sandy Creek offices.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        4
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.villageoflacona.com/about.html"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "Lacona’s heritage includes dairy farming, water‑powered mills, and lumber manufacturing that once fueled the local economy.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        18
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.villageoflacona.com/about.html"
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "text": "Lacona is surrounded by forests and farm fields, making it an idyllic spot a short drive from Oswego, Watertown, and Syracuse via I‑81 and State Routes 3 and 11.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        22
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
